# Security Practices

## Token & Session Storage
- Access tokens: in-memory only (`src/auth/token-store.ts`) — never `localStorage`
- Refresh tokens: `sessionStorage` by default; `localStorage` only when user checks "Remember me"
- MFA ticket: `sessionStorage` only — clear after successful verify
- Never log tokens, refresh tokens, MFA tickets, TOTP secrets, or recovery codes

## API Requests
- Use `apiFetch` from `src/api/client.ts` for `/api/v1` calls — handles Bearer auth + 401 refresh retry
- Always `credentials: 'include'` for cookie-based SSO (`iam_session`)
- OIDC browser login (`/oidc/login`): send `X-CSRF-Token` from `prefetchCsrfToken()` — CSRF is enforced on this path
- Federation redirects: use `googleFederationUrl()` — don't hand-build OIDC URLs with user input

## Input Validation
- Validate all forms with Zod + React Hook Form before API calls
- Sanitize user-facing error messages — show `ApiError.message`, not raw stack traces
- Encode path params in admin API URLs (`encodeURIComponent`)

## Environment & Secrets
- Only `VITE_*` vars are exposed to the browser — never put secrets in Vite env
- Align with backend: `VITE_DEFAULT_TENANT_ID`, `VITE_GOOGLE_FEDERATION_ENABLED`, proxy target
- Production: serve SPA on same origin as API (see `deployments/caddy/Caddyfile`, `README.md`)

## XSS & DOM Safety
- Avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless absolutely necessary and sanitized
- Don't inject user input into `window.location` without validation (OIDC `return_to` comes from backend redirect)

## Error Handling
- Never expose internal backend details in UI copy
- Handle 401 on protected routes via guards + token refresh; redirect to `/login` when refresh fails
